        <h2 style="text-align:center;font-size: 22px;color:cyan;">Mushroom Curry</h2>
        <img style="padding-left:225px;width:400px;height:400px" src="https://media.istockphoto.com/id/1147258041/photo/mushroom-curry-with-spinach-and-chickpeas-close-up-in-a-pan-on-the-table-vertical-top-view.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=uBEs_kmS_faJE--HwoT2nMa6xNWQerw9vHlcABuUOX0=" alt="Mushroom Curry">

        <div id="en">
            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Ingredients:</p>
            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px">  For the Mushroom Marinade:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li> 250g mushrooms, cleaned and sliced</li>
                <li> 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
                <li> Salt to taste</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px">  For the Curry:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li> 2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
                <li> 1 large onion and 2 tomatoes, finely chopped</li>
                <li> 2 green chilies, slit</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon cumin seeds, 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon coriander powder,1/2 teaspoon cumin powder</li>
                <li> 1/2 teaspoon red chili powder,1/2 teaspoon garam masala powder </li>
                <li> 1/2 cup fresh cream,1/2 cup water </li>
                <li> Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
                <li> Salt to taste</li>
            </ul>


            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Instructions:</p>
            <br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">1. Marinate the Mushrooms:</li><ul>
                <li> In a bowl, combine the cleaned and sliced mushrooms with turmeric powder and salt.</li>
                <li> Allow them to marinate for about 15-20 minutes.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">2. Sauté the Mushrooms:</li><ul>
                <li> Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a pan over medium-high heat.</li>
                <li> Add the marinated mushrooms and sauté until they release their moisture and turn golden brown.</li>
                <li> Remove them from the pan and set aside.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">3. Prepare the Curry:</li><ul>
                <li> In the same pan, add the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil.</li>
                <li> Add cumin seeds and let them splutter. </li>
                <li> Add finely chopped onions and green chilies. Sauté until the onions become translucent.</li>


            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">4. Add Ginger-Garlic Paste and Spices:</li><ul>
                <li> Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté for a couple of minutes until the raw smell disappears.</li>
                <li> Add coriander powder, cumin powder, red chili powder, and salt.</li>
                <li> Stir well and cook for a few minutes until the spices are well incorporated.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">5. Add Tomatoes:</li><ul>
                <li> Add the finely chopped tomatoes and cook until they become soft and the oil starts to separate from the mixture.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">6. Add Sautéed Mushrooms:</li><ul>
                <li> Return the sautéed mushrooms to the pan and mix them with the onion-tomato mixture.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">7. Pour in Cream:</li><ul>
                <li> Add fresh cream (or coconut milk for a vegan version) and stir well.</li>
                <li> This gives the curry a rich and creamy texture.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">8. Add Water:</li><ul>
                <li> Pour in water to achieve your desired curry consistency. Adjust the amount of water as needed.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">9. Simmer and Garnish:</li><ul>
                <li> Allow the Mushroom Curry to simmer over low heat for about 5-7 minutes to let the flavors meld.</li>
                <li> Sprinkle garam masala powder and garnish with fresh coriander leaves.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">10. Serve:</li><ul>
                <li> Serve the Mushroom Curry hot with steamed rice, naan, roti, or bread of your choice.</li>
            </ul><p style="color:orange;font-size:20px"> Enjoy your homemade Mushroom Curry, which is both creamy and full of flavor!</p>
